SIMPLE: fashionable
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fashionable
<hw>Fash"ion*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Conforming to the fashion or established mode; according with the
prevailing form or style; <as>as, a <ex>fashionable</ex>
dress</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Established or favored by custom or use; current;
prevailing at a particular time; <as>as, the <ex>fashionable</ex>
philosophy; <ex>fashionable</ex> opinions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Observant of the fashion or customary mode; dressing
or behaving according to the prevailing fashion; <as>as, a
<ex>fashionable</ex> man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Genteel; well-bred; <as>as, <ex>fashionable</ex>
society</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Time is like a <qex>fashionable</qex> host⟦br⟧
That slightly shakes his parting guest by the hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fashionable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fashionable
<hw>Fash"ion*a*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who conforms to the
fashions; -- used chiefly in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fashionableness</ent>⟦br⟧
